                            **// Realease notes //**

		// The third title in Sonys popular Crash Bandicoot series, 
                   Crash Bandicoot 3 is the first to feature 
		   Coco as a playable character, and uses the &quot;tunnel&quot; 
                   3D popularized in the earlier Crash games. As in 
		   Crash Bandicoot 2 you have to collect 25 crystals that 
                   are scattered across time before your enemy Dr. Neo Cortex does. 
		   But this time the evil witch doctor Uka Uka is with Cortex 
                   to find the crystals and take over the world.

		   With help from N. Tropy they build a Time Twister Machine 
                   to travel through time with. Crash and Coco must also use 
		   the Time Twister for gathering crystals, as usual with the 
                   help from the good witch doctor Aku Aku. But there are also 
		   42 gems scattered across time, just like in Crash 2. You must
                   find them as well in order to complete the game. 

		   When you have collected all of the 25 crystals, then you can
                   take on Cortex and Uka Uka.  //



